cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.IT 

This paper deals with linear stochastic approximation algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves the analysis of mean squared error and step-size tuning, which are related to the fields of signal processing and information theory, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory) possible categories as well.
